Model (\ref{eq12}) and (\ref{eq13}) define the likelihood of observations, $y_k$, given $x_{t_k}$ and $\theta$ --- $p(y_k|x_{t_k},\theta)$ --- as a log normal distribution with mean $\mu_Y,$ which is two-by-one vector and the standard deviation, $\Sigma_Y$, which is a two-by-two diagonal matrix with diagonal element equal to $\sigma_I$ and $\sigma_D$.  
